description:
The Job
Be our expert in using data from various sources with understanding of the process, business model, operating direction of the company’s services to measure/ analyse business performance and improve efficiency, optimize costs, maximize revenue and profit;
Work directly with the database, interact with various team to maintain stable use and data usage purposes of business and finance and accounting departments;
Responsible for calculating and extracting visual data of accounting and financial data;
Understand the customer journey, thereby proposing solutions (FinTech / Banking…) to digitize the company's business activities more clearly and improve the customer experience;
Monthly and weekly reports on the company's financial situation or when there is a big change in the company's business situation;
Provide in-depth market and competitor analysis then provide business recommendations;
Monitor the pricing of Key Accounts (specific guidelines will be provided later), create pricing scenarios and provide corresponding advice to the commercial team.
Control promotional expenses relating to user and driver incentives, conduct a deep dive into budget allocation.
Monitor SG&A costs against the budget through contract reviews based on an internal system.
Such monitoring actions mentioned as aboved should be closely to MIS report i.e. Management Information Report
Assist in other tasks required by Finance & Accounting Manager (if any)
Your skills and Experience
Bachelor's degree or equivalent in Finance, Economics, Business Administration or equivalent knowledge;
At least 3 years’ experience in a related position (experienced in technology companies: Big4, On-demand, eCommerce, Fintech, Games preferred);
Having in-depth knowledge of Finance and Accounting;
Having data analysis skills, proficient in using Google Tools, Excel, SQL, Python and a good command in presentation skills
Excellent problem-solving skills;
Do not hesitate to changes and appreciate innovation at work

Company Description
We help grow many of the world's most iconic brands at Leo Burnett. We help grow even more of the world's most talented people. You'll find at Leo Burnett an agency built on ideas and dependent upon the people behind them. A culture that doesn't just respect creativity but cherishes it. And a community where the path you choose is your own, the places you can go limitless. We believe creativity has the power to transform human behavior, and we use ours to help our clients' brands discover their "human purpose" and play meaningful, active roles in people's lives.
Job Description
Developing and prospecting new business;
Providing effective services to all clients assigned and managing each account professionally and efficiently;
Being on the alert to problems and opportunities, both for the agency and clients;
Have strong independence, at the same time a team-player;
Managing report assigned and can lead and grow the team;
Recommending and implementing cost control measures;
QC and inputting on works done by creative, studio, media, strategy before presenting to client;
Liaising and integrating different internal disciplines, as well as external partners and suppliers;
Managing timeline, budget, KPIs and operations for communications campaigns;
Doing billing and income forecasts quarterly or as directed and checking monthly actual versus forecast;
Staying up-to-date on the business, market, and competitors;
Performing tasks as delegated by line managers.

Qualifications
Bachelor’s or above
3+ years in advertising/ communications/ marketing/ account management, with IMC & Digital experience
Proactive, agile, professional.
Responsible, resilient, attention to details
Ability to handle rapidly changing environment.
Ability to work independently under high pressure.
Excellent English communication (written and oral) skills.

