Support FM to prepare the standard documentation for monthly reports and routine transactions to provide details guidelines and checklist for execution and follow-up;
2) Cash-flow management:
Keep track of the actual cash flow to identify any significant variance between the actual spending and obtain the understanding from PIC in order to analyze and forecast the cash-flow trend; bring the determined issues to the Finance Manager for further actions if required;
Prepare liquidation report and review with Finance Manager before sending to General Accounting team for monthly report submission;
Manage the cash position of each currency in line with the cash requirements to ensure that there is no issue with a payment schedule;
Align the interco payment schedule with other entities to ensure that there are no mismatches in interco balance and any old-aged items are under control with agreement from FMs and RFD;
3) Accounts Payables:
Manage accounts payables using ERP (M3) system;
Provide on-job training about tax and accounting regulations for AP team members to ensure that the supporting documents received follow regulations as well as minimize the volume of the non-deductible expenses in CIT calculation, highlight documents being subject to FCT and share with the General accounting team for review and calculating FCT;
Process transactions and perform accounting duties such as: checking documents to ensure that they are compliant with Company policy and current effective regulations and standards; recording entries on a timely basis; and filing documents into Proxess on time;
Reconcile AP breakdown with TB before and after revaluation;
Complete steps on the AP side for a month-close process;
Establish and maintain relationships with new and existing vendors;
Propose improvements in the AP process to increase the efficiency and effectiveness of the Internal control system;
Support the Finance Manager in controlling and implementing new projects of AP function;
Prepare monthly reports for AP function for review and analysis in order to manage the old-aged items, and issues pending and identify process gaps to be improved;
4) Bank transactions:
Support Finance manager to deal with banks for FX rate and time deposit rate;
Coordinate with banks to process transactions/update the Company information as per request on time;
Prepare payment list on time and review supporting documents transferred from AP Team to ensure that they are properly and comply with regulations (accounting, tax, and foreign currency management);
Review and ensure there is no issue in bank information of transactions proposed in the payment list;
5) Accounting:
Update payment transactions into TM5 & ERP system on time in order to provide timely data for reporting;
Reconcile cash/bank as per the agreed month-close deadline and ensure that cash/bank balance is matched with accounting book and TM5 system;
Post accruals for expenses relating to Treasury function as per agreed month-close deadline;
Prepare the Loan breakdown report for control loan movements as well as interest expense for payment and accruals;
Support FM and General accounting team to prepare data and documents for statutory audit and tax audit;
6) Loans management:
Register long-term loans or the extension of a short-term loan to a long-term loan with the State Bank of Vietnam (SBV) and update any amendments as required by regulations;
Prepare the monthly/annual performance of borrowing and repayment of offshore loan reports as per requirement of SBV
Control the loan repayment and loan interest payment schedule and prepare the payment documents properly and on time
7) Budgeting:
Prepare the loan interest expenses for budget and forecast I, II, and III activities;
Propose the budget for bank charges and other expenses for Treasury function (if any);
8) Other adhoc as assigned by direct supervisor and line manager
Job Specification
Bachelor's Degree in Finance and Accounting
At least 7-10 years of working experience in the relevant fields
Good command of English (both verbal and written skills)
Good knowledge of Tax and Accounting; working with SBV and commercial banks; and regulations on foreign currency management and offshore loan management
Good understanding of VAS, taxation, especially in CIT, FCT, and invoicing
Experience in ERP system, especially in Finance module
